{"word":"χλαμύς","slug":"χλαμύς","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b><el>χλαμύς, ύδος, ἡ</el></b> [<a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ perh.\">perh.</a> of foreign <a class=\"G\" href=\"S:✎ orig.\">orig.</a>] <b>cloak,</b> the qualifier <el><a class=\"S\" href=\"S:κόκκινος\">κόκκινος</a></el> red, scarlet indicates that the <el>χ.</el> is the cheaply dyed garment worn by soldiers <b><a href='B:470 27:28'>Mt 27:28</a>, <a href='B:470 27:31'>31</a>.</b> <center id=\"nav_bottom\"> <a id=\"left_arrow\" href=\"S:χιών\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> <a id=\"bottom_home\" href=\"S:#1.Table of Contents\">&emsp;&emsp;</a> <a id=\"right_arrow\" href=\"S:χλευάζω\">&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;&ensp;</a> </center> "}]}